\n     /dev/cdrom represent your CD-ROM\n    /dev/fd0 represent floppy disk \n\n/lost+found\n  Sometimes your system might crash or a power failure might take the machine down. Either way, at the next boot, a lengthy filesystem check using fsck will be done.\n    The files recovered are not likely to be complete\n      but there always is a chance that something worthwhile is recovered\n  Each partition has its own lost+found directory\n    If you find files in there, try to move them back to their original location\n\n/mnt\n  u should mount ur devices here like cd\n    mount /dev/cdrom /mnt/cdrom\n\n/proc\n  It doesn_t contain _real_ files but runtime system information\n    e.g. system memory, devices mounted, hardware configuration, etc\n  for the information centre for the kernel\n  e.g   \'lsmod\' is the same as \'cat /proc/modules\' while \'lspci\' is a synonym for \'cat /proc/pci\'\n\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(108,'to #extract some range of lines in file00 #sed',NULL,'sed -n 2,4p file00',NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(109,'#mplayer #interval_playing',NULL,NULL,'\nto run a media from 90sec and 30sec which are after\n  mplayer -ss 90 -endpos 30 file00.mp3\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(110,'#youtube-dl #install ',NULL,NULL,'\nhttp://rg3.github.io/youtube-dl/download.html\n\n  sudo curl https://yt-dl.org/downloads/2015.01.08/youtube-dl -o /usr/local/bin/youtube-dl\n  sudo chmod a+x /usr/local/bin/youtube-dl\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(111,'#ffprobe #install',NULL,NULL,'this is installed with ffmpeg\n  apt-get install ffmpeg\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(112,'#os#installation',NULL,NULL,'tune2fs -l /dev/sda5 |grep  \'Filesystem created\'\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(113,'#latest_created_file #linux #ls',NULL,'ls -1t | head -1',NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(114,'#linux #readlink',NULL,NULL,'readlink -f file00\n  to get the fullpath of file00','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(115,'-find #linux simple',NULL,NULL,'find /path/folder00 -iname \'*pattern00*\'\n  to find file_folder