nformation or data that the company values most\n    When you exploit one system after another, you are trying to demonstrate attacks that would have the greatest business impact\n\n  Reporting\n    use reports to communicate what you did, how you did it, and, most impor- tant, how the organization should fix it\n    At a minimum,\n      divide your report into an \n        executive summary, \n        executive presentation, \n        and technical findings\n          will be used by the client to remediate security holes\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(138,'#ptes #types #intro #2types','\novert pentesting\n  u have access from the organisation to pentest the sys of the org00\n  then, u have many information about the org_target\n\ncovert pentesting\n  to attack or to simulate an attacker towards an organisation\n    without the knowledge for the org_target that they are attacked :/\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(139,'#linux #group #list',NULL,NULL,'cut -d: -f1 /etc/group\n  that is to list all group in ur sys','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(140,'#linux #user #list',NULL,NULL,'\ncut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd\n  to list all user in ur linux','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(141,'#linux #user #create#useradd',NULL,NULL,'\nuseradd -d /path/home_user00 user00\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(142,'#linux #create#user #specifi#uid#useradd',NULL,NULL,'useradd -u 127 user00','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(143,'#linux #create#user #specifi#gid#useradd',NULL,NULL,'useradd -u 1000 -g 500 user00','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(144,'#create#user to #multiple#groups',NULL,NULL,'useradd -G grp00,grp01,grp02 user00','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(145,'#user to #check in #multiple#groups #id',NULL,NULL,'id user00','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(146,'#useradd #create#user #specific#group',NULL,'useradd -G grp00 user00',NULL,'2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(147,'#linux #make a #user #sudoer',NULL,NULL,'edit:/etc/sudoers\n  add\n  user00 ALL=(ALL) ALL\n','2015-02-07 06:36:13'),(148,'#linux #cut #delimiter #column',NULL,NULL,'ls -l|cut -d