her(phoenix, winter, warm).\n		phoenix is warm in the winter\n\nvi /path/rules_prolog.pl','2015-02-15 08:56:59'),(675,'#gnuprologjava -start -intro -long-list',NULL,NULL,'\nto load facts:\nmake sure that \"fact_rule.pl\"\n    is in the same folder as this code_of_java\n    \'\n    import gnu.prolog.term.AtomTerm;\n    import gnu.prolog.vm.Environment;\n    \'\n    main() {\n        ...\n        Environment env = new Environment();\n        env.ensureLoaded(AtomTerm.get(\"fact_rule.pl\"));\n        ...\n    }\n\n\nafter loading the fact_rule.pl\nu need to get _interperter_ used to execute goals of your question.\n    \'\n    import gnu.prolog.vm.Interperter;\n    \'\n    main(){\n        ...\n        Interpreter interpreter;\n            // u can not create an object of class Interpreter\n        interpreter = env.createInterpreter();\n            // env is already defined before\n        ...\n    }\n\nafter the load of fact_rule, and setting the interperter_\nu need to initialise\n    \'\n    ...\n    env.runInitialization(interpreter);\n    ...\n\nnow the setup is completed\nu can start running goals like this next one:\n    \'\n    ...\n    interpreter.runOnce(Term);\n        // Term is the goal u want to exe\n    ...\n\n#end_file\n','2015-03-07 16:12:37'),(676,'#prolog -comment in-fact',NULL,NULL,'\nthis next is a fact of prolog\n	child(person01, person02).\n	  % this is a comment\n	  % person01 is a child of person02\n	parent(person02, person01).\n	  % this is a comment\n	  % person02 is a parent of person01\n','2015-02-14 01:56:28'),(673,'#prolog -intro -long-list',NULL,NULL,'\nc un langage:\n    declaratif(contrairement a java, cpp, ...(langage imperatif))\n    indeterministe(permet de traiter pbm comportant plusieurs solutions)\n\non trouve tjr:\n    connaissance(decrivant des faits )     --+--- ces 2 ensembles forment la base des\n        regroupes dans une base de faits     |        connaissances\n    des regles                             --+  \n    moteur