s finally{ ... }\n','2015-02-22 01:16:16'),(787,'#des_p -type','\nhttp://www.tutorialspoint.com/design_pattern/design_pattern_overview.htm\ncreational patterns\n    provide a way to create obj while hide the creation logic\n\nstructural patterns\n    concern class and object composition\n    concept of inheritance is used to compose interface\n        then define ways to compose objects\n\nbehavioral patterns\n    concerned with communication between objects.   \n\nj2ee pattern\n    concerned with the presentation tier\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-22 05:48:41'),(788,'#des_p -glimpse','\nfactory pattern\nabstract factory pattern\nsingleton pattern\nbuilder pattern\nprototype pattern\nadapter pattern\nbridge pattern\nfilter pattern\ncomposite pattern\nfacade pattern\nflyweight pattern\nproxy pattern\n\ncommand pattern\ninterpreter pattern\niterator pattern\nmediator pattern\nmemento pattern\nobserver pattern\nstate pattern\nnull object pattern\nstategy pattern\ntemplate pattern\nvisitor pattern\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-22 05:57:33'),(789,'#java -variables -pass_by-reference -by-value','Objects and primitives are passed by value',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-22 06:41:09'),(790,'#java -class-loader','\nThe very first class is especially loaded with \"static main()\"\n	All the subsequently classes will be loaded from the classes in that meth\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-22 06:46:41'),(791,'#uml -intro','\numl was created by omg in 1997\numl is a pictorial language used to make software blue prints\n\nit is mostly used to model software sys\n    but it can model non software systems as well like process flow in a manufacturing unit\n\ngoals:\n====================================\nA picture is worth a thousand words\n\nto define some general purpose(idea)\n    the idea will be easy to understand and to use\n\nUML diagrams are not only made for developers but also for business users\n    The system can be a software or non software.\n\nUML describes the real time systems\n\n\n\n\na conceptual model is required\n    a model which is made of concepts and the relationships of those concepts.\n    the first step before drawing a UML diagram.\n        It helps to understand the entities in the real world and how they interact with each other.\n    \'\n    as uml describes the real time systems, then the conceptual model will be done gradually\n    \'\n    conceptual model of uml can be mastered by understanding the following 3elts:\n        uml building blocks\n        rules to connect the building blocks\n        common mechanisms of uml\n\n\n\n\noo concepts:\n    objects contains both data and methods(control the data)\n        data(represents the state of the object)\n    objects are the real world entities\n    \'\n    Following are some fundamental concepts of object oriented world\n        objects\n        class\n        abstraction:    represents the behavior of an real world entity\n        encapsulation:  the mechanism of binding the data together and hiding them from outside world.\n        inheritance:    the mechanism of making new classes from existing one\n        polymorphism:   defines the mechanism to exists in different forms\n\n\n\noo analysis and design\n    oo_analysis:    the investigation of objects\n    design:         the collaboration of identified objects\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-22 06:49:44'),(792,'#fs -mmt|nonickn-file-architecture','\nthe uuid will be get by using:\n    blkid\nsome information will be gotten from\n    df\n    fdik -l\n\nhere I will try to define how all my files are saved in my hdds:\nI have 3 hdds:\n    little_seagate(320G)\n    sn: W045P05A\n        84G\n            /media/03542841-3000-4d54-8be0-36331794bb72\n            uuid:   416f5a0d-b6d2-4f44-84ae-a1c2166d5bb9\n        21G\n            /media/a6a5a339-67d7-4b08-98c9-5ff3f153c7ca\n            uuid:   208a16d7-719c-4cb8-910b-784a3becf466\n        105G\n            /media/2b023182-a68c-480f-8f7f-e4925fe84c7f\n            uuid:   2b023182-a68c-480f-8f7f-e4925fe84c7f\n 