s_identity are used, and they are used in different phases of call setup\n\'\nimsi is the first nb_identity of the subscriber\n    it is assigned permanently to that subscriber\n    \'\n    imsi = mcc + mnc + msin\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 03:18:14'),(865,'#mysql -column-change|modify|rename',NULL,NULL,'\nboth change and modify are able to change the description of a col\n\'\nalter table table00 change column col00 col01 descr_col;\n    used if u want to _rename_ the col00 \n\nalter table table00 modify column col00 descr_col;\n    used if u don_t want to change the name of the col\n\n\'\nexp:\n    alter table person change name real_name text;\n','2015-02-28 03:50:56'),(866,'#gsm -sim -intro','\nused to route the call\n\nused to perform billing\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 03:57:09'),(867,'#gsm -identification','\nimsi is the first nb used for the identification\n    it is transmitted in the initialization of the mobile\n\'\nafter sending imsi\n    tmsi is sent and updated periodically:\n        bcz of the security\n        with the lai\n\nmsisdn is used to identify a subscriber everywhere in the world (ifk)\n\nsubscriber authentication key(ki) (to search)\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 04:05:11'),(868,'#telec -drive-test','\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drive_testing\nDrive testing is a method of measuring and assessing the coverage, capacity and Quality of Service (QoS) of a mobile radio network\n\nhttp://www.telecomhall.com/what-is-rf-drive-test-testing-.aspx\nit  is the procedure to perform a test while driving\nyou can do a drive test using a motorcycle or bicycle.\n    What matters is the hardware and software used in the test\n    \'\n    the following is the schematic of the std_connections:\n\n                                                                +-----------+\n                                                                |  scanner  |\n                                                                +----+------+\n                                        +----+                       |\n                         +-----+        | pc |                       |\n                         | gps +--------+----+-----------------------+\n                         +-----+       /    /            +--------+\n                                      ------+--+     +---| dongle |\n                                               |     |   +--------+\n                                               +-----+\n                                                     |\n                                                     |    +--+\n                                                     +----|ms|\n                                                          +--+ \n\nthe pc will output sth like the follows;\n    \n              |           |\n              |<--Road--->|       +----  ms   : signal level - best server --+\n              |           |       |                ........                  |\n              |           |       |                                          +-- output file\n         +----+       +---+       +---- gps   : latitude - longitude         |\n         |            |           |                .........                 |      of\n         |    +-+     |           |                                          |\n         |    |x+-----------------+----- scanner : other servers             |    the pc\n         |    +-+     |                            .........               --+\n         |            |\n   ------+     +------+\n               |\n               |\n   ------------+\nGPS: collecting the data of latitude and longitude of each point\n    and more things, but those are the most important\n\'\nms: mobile data collections, such as signal strength,\n    best_server\n\'\nscanner:    collecting data throughout the network\n\nCurrently, there are already cell phones that do everything.\n    They have a GPS,\n    collection of specific software\n    \'\n    but they are very expensive\n\nSTEPS:\n    The routes are predefined in the office\n        it indicates where testing will occur.\n        \'\n        This area is defined based on several factors, mainly related to the purpose of the test.\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 15:41:02'),(869,'#gsm -main-signalling-channels','\nhttp://www.whytelecom.com/content/signaling-channel-gsm-radio-interface\nbch\n    transmitted by the bts to the ms\n    it carries sys_param\n    bcch\n    fcch\n    sch\n    cbch\ncch\nsdcch\nacch\nccch\n\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-02-28 17:12:26'),(870,'#gen_c #lakh','\nA lakh or lac\nabbr L\na unit in the Indian Numbering System\nequal to one hundred thousand \n\n1L = 10^5\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 05:41:13'),(871,'#gen_c #sq.km -unit','\n1sq.km = 1km^2\n\n1sq.km = 0.3861 square miles\n         247.1 acres\n\n1 acre = about 0.004047km2, 0.4047ha or 4047 m^2\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 05:47:24'),(872,'create windows_bootable from linux','\nhttp://www.webupd8.org/2010/10/create-bootable-windows-7-usb-drive.html\n================================================================================\n\nmake sure that those next packages are installed:\n    gparted\n    ntfs-3g\n\nplug ur usb_stick\nopen gparted(Applications > Sys_tools > Administr > gparted)\nselect the usb_stick\n    (gparted > devices > /ur/usb_stick)\numount the usb_stick (from gparted)\nto format the usb_stick in ntfs_format\n    (partition > format > ntfs)\nmake the usb_will be bootable\n    right_click usb_stick\n    select Manage_flags > \"boot\"\nmount back the usb_drive\nsome users told that w7 installation fails\n    dl unetbootin version494\n        http://sourceforge.net/projects/unetbootin/files/UNetbootin/494/unetbootin-linux-494/download\n\nright_click the file just dldd\n     select (properties > permissions > allow_executing_file_as_prg)\n\ndouble_click the dldd_file\nu have the option \"show all drives\" in the 494version\n\ninstall ur windows7 onto ur usb_drive\n\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 14:16:47'),(873,'#telec -wcdma','\nwcdma technology provides some advantages for the operator \n    in that it allows the data, \n    improves the voice of base.\n\nWCDMA can offer more voice minutes with better quality\n\nVoice capacity offered is very high due to \n    interference control mechanisms, \n    including frequency reuse of 1, \n    fast power control, \n    and soft handover.\n\nwcdma improves broadband voice service with amr_codec\n\nwcdma provides better capacity of the bts \n    and the efficiency of the equipment\n\na large number of users are supported by the carrier\n    with less rf_carriers required\n\nwcdma operators are able to provide useful data_services:\n    navigation\n    person to person video_calls\n    tv_clips\n\nit enables simultaneously voice and data\n\nthe operators offer moblie connectivity to the internet \n    with maximum bit_rate of 384kbps downlink and uplink\n\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 14:57:23'),(874,'#telec -hspa -hsdpa-hsupa','\nhspa = hsupa + hsdpa \n\nThe HSDPA peak data rate available in the terminals is initially 1.8Mbps\n    it is increasing and later it will be beyond 10MBps\n\nThe HSUPA peak data rate in the initial phase was 1–2 Mbps and the second phase was 3–4Mbps\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 15:07:13'),(875,'#by_me -sys playlist -important','\ni decided to put all vid in /hddXX/vid\nto make it easy to access,\n    i use files for the playlist\n\nall playlist_file will start with:\n    pl\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-01 16:46:47'),(876,'files and its extension','\nvideo:\n    webm\n    3gp\n    mp4\n    avi\n    flv\n#end_video\n\naudio:\n    mp3\n    wav\n    ogg\n#end_audio\n\npic:\n    gif\n    jpg\n    jpeg\n#end_pic\n',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-02 01:58:05'),(877,'vlc features',NULL,NULL,'\nhttp://www.howtogeek.com/173222/10-useful-features-hidden-in-vlc-the-swiss-army-knife-of-media-players/\n','2015-03-01 17:09:05'),(878,'#linuxfork bomb',NULL,':(){ :|: & };:',NULL,'2015-03-01 17:26:16'),(879,'#linux rm_-rf_/',NULL,NULL,'\nrm -rf / \n	could be disguised in hexadecimal, this is the hexa