ravel to all parts of your body to maintain your tissues and organs\nYour endocrine system is made of many glands and organs. They have different functions, and work together to keep you healthy.\nhttp://www.hormone.org/hormones-and-health/the-endocrine-system\n','2015-01-21 10:54:19'),(44,'#endocrine_sys #intro #glands(some)','\nThe endocrine system controls the way your body functions. It produces hormones that travel to all parts of your body to maintain your tissues and organs.\nHere are a few of the areas governed by the endocrine system:\n    Reproduction\n    Responses to stress and injury\n    Growth and sexual development\n    Body energy levels\n    Internal balance of body systems\n    Bone and muscle strength\n\nYour endocrine system produces, stores and releases hormones. When everything goes smoothly, your body functions properly.\n\nYour endocrine system is made of many glands and organs.\nThese are the glands of your endocrine system:\n	Adrenal glands - influence the way your body uses energy, \n		release the adrenaline_hormone when u_re under_stress\n	Hypothalamus - part of your brain that controls hormone production\n	Ovaries\n	Pancreas\n		releases the insulin your body needs to metabolize sugar;\n	Parathyroid \n		located behind the thyroid gland,\n	Pineal gland\n		connects the endocrine system with the nervous system;\n		produces several hormone(ex: melatonin: important to sleep/wake cycles and sexual development)\n	Pituitary gland \n		likely the most important gland in your body, it is crucial to growth, mental development and reproduction\n	Testes\n		 produce the hormone testosterone(maintains sperm production and bone mass)\n	Thymus\n		crucial to normal immune function in childhood\n	Thyroid gland\n		located in the front of your neck, it releases hormones that control your metabolism and govern the way your body uses energy\n','2015-01-21 11:12:33'),(45,'#endocrine_sys gland#role','\nPituitary Gland:\n	often referred to as the \"master gland\"\n	produces several hormones:\n		Growth hormone:\n			promotes growth in childhood\n			For adults, it helps to maintain healthy muscle and bone mass\n		Prolactin:\n			In women, it stimulates milk production\n			In males, low levels are linked to sexual problems\n				most males make no use of the hormone\n		Oxytocin\n			causes pregnant women to start having contractions at the appropriate time and also promotes milk flow in nursing mothers\n		Antidiuretic hormone\n			Commonly referred to as vasopressin, this hormone helps to regulate water balance in the body\n		Adrenocorticotropic\n			promotes the production of cortisol, which helps to reduce stress, maintain healthy blood pressure and more\n		Thyroid-stimulating hormone\n			Just as the name implies\n		Luteinizing hormone\n			In women, this hormone regulates estrogen\n			In men, it regulates testosterone.\n		Follicle-stimulating hormone\n			It stimulates the releasing of eggs in women\n			ensure the normal function of sperm production in men\n','2015-01-21 11:32:00'),(46,'#some_important#hormones','\nirisin\nparathyroid\ntestosterone\npeptideYY\nglucagon-like-peptide\ninsulin\nglucagon\nserotonin\ngherlin\nleptin\nadiponectin\nmelatonin:	responsible of:\noxytocin\ngrowth hormone\ncortisol\nadrenaline\n	also called epinephrine\ndopamine\nthyroxin\n','2015-01-22 12:23:02'),(47,'#hormone_melatonin','responsible of:\n	drowsy feeling, it makes you fall asleep\n','2015-01-22 12:01:37'),(48,'#hormone_serotonin','\nresponsible of:\n	mood\n	appetite\n	sleep cycles\n','2015-01-22 12:07:21'),(49,'#hormone#noradrenaline','\nalso called norepinephrine\nresponsible of:\n	blood pressure\n	contributes to the control of sleep\nctrl the heart, emotions\n\ntoo much gives you an anxious feeling\ntoo little can leave you feeling depressed\n','2015-01-22 13:16:28'),(50,'#hormone#adiponectine','\na protein hormone\nregulates metabolic processes \n	such as the regulation of glucose. \n','2015-01-22 13:18:00'),(51,'#hormone#adiponectine','\na